TIGRE (Tiny Graphics Rendering Engine)

What is Tigre ?
================

Tigre is a set of libraries dedicated to advanced visualization and/or 
video game development.

Tigre is free, open source and cross-platform.

Philosphy
==========

Antoine de Saint-Exupéry said :

"A designer knows he has achieved perfection not when there is nothing 
left to add, but when there is nothing left to take away.”

Tigre is designed to be simple before everything else.

Platforms
==========

- Linux
- Android
- Windows

It should be easy to port the engine on any platform that supports C++.

License
========
TIGRE is made available under the MIT License.

